                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48/2608: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Colonel <persName type="to">E. M. House</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-05T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 5, 1918—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>127. [From President Wilson.] Please let Mr. Hoover know that, very much to my
                    regret, I fear that the terms of the appropriation for National Security and
                    Defence would not justify my making the allotment to which he refers. Woodrow
                        Wilson.<note n="22" xml:id="d537fn22">See Colonel House’s telegram No. 214,
                        Dec. 1, 1918, 10 p.m., <ref target="#pg_645">p. 645</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
